h kids the facts and teach them to critically think and come to their own conclusions. We now spoon feed them with political correct extremism and force the kids to conform to liberal thinking- even to contradict the parents' education and values. Is it any surprise that the next generation are growing up confused. It is a school's place to teach my child math, English, History and equip him with KNOWLEDGE. It is not the school's place to teach children morality and values or &quot;protect&quot; our children&quot; by never failing them or teaching them how to spell because it isn't important.. It is our job as parents to teach our children values and morality. Don't take that away from us. . "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="983" language="en" documentId="1482" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="MickeyMe" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1482" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="983"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>